{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778983383443,"sessionID":"ses_1cc5be10bffeihXrzY1FV2TH0l","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_lyeRdGfXBZPTItEWaiFoDBYT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+## PMID:25327288 \"Selective VPS34 inhibitor blocks autophagy and uncovers a role for NCOA4 in ferritin degradation and iron homeostasis in vivo.\"\n+\n+This paper provides the core evidence that ferritin is degraded through a selective autophagy pathway involving NCOA4 and FTH1, linking the process to iron homeostasis.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:25327288 \"NCOA4 directly binds ferritin heavy chain-1 (FTH1) to target the iron-binding ferritin complex with a relative molecular mass of 450,000 to autolysosomes following starvation or iron depletion.\"\n+  - Supports that ferritin is a selective cargo for autophagic degradation.\n+  - Supports NCOA4 and FTH1 as key components of the process.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:25327288 \"Taken together, the results of this study provide a new mechanism for selective autophagy of ferritin and reveal a previously unappreciated role for autophagy and NCOA4 in the control of iron homeostasis in vivo.\"\n+  - Supports the process as a selective autophagy pathway.\n+  - Supports the biological outcome of regulating iron availability.\n+\n+## PMID:26436293 \"Ferritinophagy via NCOA4 is required for erythropoiesis and is regulated by iron dependent HERC2-mediated proteolysis.\"\n+\n+This paper validates ferritinophagy as established terminology and provides additional evidence that NCOA4 is the selective cargo receptor delivering ferritin for lysosomal degradation.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:26436293 \"NCOA4 is a selective cargo receptor for the autophagic turnover of ferritin, a process critical for regulation of intracellular iron bioavailability.\"\n+  - Supports use of the name ferritinophagy.\n+  - Supports the process definition as selective autophagic degradation of ferritin.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:26436293 \"we demonstrate that direct association via a key surface arginine in FTH1 and a C-terminal element in NCOA4 is required for delivery of ferritin to the lysosome via autophagosomes.\"\n+  - Supports that the process proceeds through macroautophagy/autophagosome-mediated delivery.\n+\n+## PMID:38714719 \"Structural basis for the intracellular regulation of ferritin degradation.\"\n+\n+This recent paper provides an up-to-date wording for the process and reinforces that ferritinophagy is a ferritin-specific autophagic pathway releasing stored iron.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:38714719 \"The binding of NCOA4 to the FTH1 subunits of ferritin initiates ferritinophagy-a ferritin-specific autophagic pathway leading to the release of the iron stored inside ferritin.\"\n+  - Supports the synonym \"ferritin-specific autophagy\" from the issue body.\n+  - Supports the process outcome of releasing iron stored in ferritin.\n+\n+## Curation conclusion\n+\n+- The requested term is supported by the literature and by current community usage of the label \"ferritinophagy\".\n+- Parentage under `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy` is supported by precedent for cargo-specific selective autophagy terms and by the cited literature describing delivery via autophagosomes/autolysosomes.\n+- A concise GO-style definition consistent with current precedent is: \"The selective degradation of ferritin by macroautophagy.\" with support from PMID:25327288, PMID:26436293, and PMID:38714719.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+# Ferritinophagy term pattern notes\n+\n+## Relevant precedent in GO\n+\n+Existing cargo-specific macroautophagy terms use a lightweight asserted pattern rather than a DOSDP-backed logical definition.\n+\n+- `GO:0034517` ribophagy\n+  - def: \"The selective degradation of mature ribosomes by macroautophagy.\"\n+  - parent: `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy`\n+- `GO:0035973` aggrephagy\n+  - def: \"The selective degradation of protein aggregates by macroautophagy.\"\n+  - parent: `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy`\n+- `GO:0061724` lipophagy\n+  - def: \"The selective degradation of lipid droplets by macroautophagy.\"\n+  - parent: `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy`\n+- `GO:0061816` proteaphagy\n+  - def: \"The selective degradation of proteasomes by macroautophagy.\"\n+  - parent: `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy`\n+- `GO:0062093` lysophagy\n+  - def: \"The selective autophagy process in which a damaged lysosome is degraded by macroautophagy.\"\n+  - parent: `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy`\n+\n+## Pattern decision for this issue\n+\n+- No dedicated YAML design pattern was identified under `src/patterns` for cargo-specific macroautophagy terms.\n+- The closest and best-supported pattern is existing GO precedent in `go-edit.obo`.\n+- Therefore the new term should:\n+  - use the established community label `ferritinophagy`\n+  - include the exact synonym `ferritin-specific autophagy`\n+  - use an asserted `is_a` to `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy`\n+  - avoid `intersection_of` axioms, since there is no clear existing DP and stronger equivalence would risk over-specification\n+\n+## Definition style\n+\n+Recommended GO-style definition:\n+\n+`The selective degradation of ferritin by macroautophagy.`\n+\n+This matches the wording style and granularity of ribophagy, aggrephagy, lipophagy, and proteaphagy.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770069.obo\n+[Term]\n+id: GO:7770069\n+name: ferritinophagy\n+namespace: biological_process\n+def: \"The selective degradation of ferritin by macroautophagy.\" [PMID:25327288, PMID:26436293, PMID:38714719]\n+synonym: \"ferritin-specific autophagy\" EXACT []\n+is_a: GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy\n+property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30894\" xsd:anyURI\n+created_by: dragon-ai-agent\n+creation_date: 2026-05-17T02:02:25Z\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA RESEARCH.md\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\nA terms/GO_7770069.obo","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+## PMID:25327288 \"Selective VPS34 inhibitor blocks autophagy and uncovers a role for NCOA4 in ferritin degradation and iron homeostasis in vivo.\"\n+\n+This paper provides the core evidence that ferritin is degraded through a selective autophagy pathway involving NCOA4 and FTH1, linking the process to iron homeostasis.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:25327288 \"NCOA4 directly binds ferritin heavy chain-1 (FTH1) to target the iron-binding ferritin complex with a relative molecular mass of 450,000 to autolysosomes following starvation or iron depletion.\"\n+  - Supports that ferritin is a selective cargo for autophagic degradation.\n+  - Supports NCOA4 and FTH1 as key components of the process.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:25327288 \"Taken together, the results of this study provide a new mechanism for selective autophagy of ferritin and reveal a previously unappreciated role for autophagy and NCOA4 in the control of iron homeostasis in vivo.\"\n+  - Supports the process as a selective autophagy pathway.\n+  - Supports the biological outcome of regulating iron availability.\n+\n+## PMID:26436293 \"Ferritinophagy via NCOA4 is required for erythropoiesis and is regulated by iron dependent HERC2-mediated proteolysis.\"\n+\n+This paper validates ferritinophagy as established terminology and provides additional evidence that NCOA4 is the selective cargo receptor delivering ferritin for lysosomal degradation.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:26436293 \"NCOA4 is a selective cargo receptor for the autophagic turnover of ferritin, a process critical for regulation of intracellular iron bioavailability.\"\n+  - Supports use of the name ferritinophagy.\n+  - Supports the process definition as selective autophagic degradation of ferritin.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:26436293 \"we demonstrate that direct association via a key surface arginine in FTH1 and a C-terminal element in NCOA4 is required for delivery of ferritin to the lysosome via autophagosomes.\"\n+  - Supports that the process proceeds through macroautophagy/autophagosome-mediated delivery.\n+\n+## PMID:38714719 \"Structural basis for the intracellular regulation of ferritin degradation.\"\n+\n+This recent paper provides an up-to-date wording for the process and reinforces that ferritinophagy is a ferritin-specific autophagic pathway releasing stored iron.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:38714719 \"The binding of NCOA4 to the FTH1 subunits of ferritin initiates ferritinophagy-a ferritin-specific autophagic pathway leading to the release of the iron stored inside ferritin.\"\n+  - Supports the synonym \"ferritin-specific autophagy\" from the issue body.\n+  - Supports the process outcome of releasing iron stored in ferritin.\n+\n+## Curation conclusion\n+\n+- The requested term is supported by the literature and by current community usage of the label \"ferritinophagy\".\n+- Parentage under `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy` is supported by precedent for cargo-specific selective autophagy terms and by the cited literature describing delivery via autophagosomes/autolysosomes.\n+- A concise GO-style definition consistent with current precedent is: \"The selective degradation of ferritin by macroautophagy.\" with support from PMID:25327288, PMID:26436293, and PMID:38714719.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,39 @@\n+# Ferritinophagy term pattern notes\n+\n+## Relevant precedent in GO\n+\n+Existing cargo-specific macroautophagy terms use a lightweight asserted pattern rather than a DOSDP-backed logical definition.\n+\n+- `GO:0034517` ribophagy\n+  - def: \"The selective degradation of mature ribosomes by macroautophagy.\"\n+  - parent: `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy`\n+- `GO:0035973` aggrephagy\n+  - def: \"The selective degradation of protein aggregates by macroautophagy.\"\n+  - parent: `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy`\n+- `GO:0061724` lipophagy\n+  - def: \"The selective degradation of lipid droplets by macroautophagy.\"\n+  - parent: `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy`\n+- `GO:0061816` proteaphagy\n+  - def: \"The selective degradation of proteasomes by macroautophagy.\"\n+  - parent: `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy`\n+- `GO:0062093` lysophagy\n+  - def: \"The selective autophagy process in which a damaged lysosome is degraded by macroautophagy.\"\n+  - parent: `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy`\n+\n+## Pattern decision for this issue\n+\n+- No dedicated YAML design pattern was identified under `src/patterns` for cargo-specific macroautophagy terms.\n+- The closest and best-supported pattern is existing GO precedent in `go-edit.obo`.\n+- Therefore the new term should:\n+  - use the established community label `ferritinophagy`\n+  - include the exact synonym `ferritin-specific autophagy`\n+  - use an asserted `is_a` to `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy`\n+  - avoid `intersection_of` axioms, since there is no clear existing DP and stronger equivalence would risk over-specification\n+\n+## Definition style\n+\n+Recommended GO-style definition:\n+\n+`The selective degradation of ferritin by macroautophagy.`\n+\n+This matches the wording style and granularity of ribophagy, aggrephagy, lipophagy, and proteaphagy.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770069.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770069.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_7770069.obo\n@@ -0,0 +1,10 @@\n+[Term]\n+id: GO:777