{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778983907025,"sessionID":"ses_1cc5be10bffeihXrzY1FV2TH0l","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_VKPCXJlnf7xMRwerCZPFPCx3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Added the requested term and committed the ontology change locally.\n+\n+Summary:\n+- Added `ferritinophagy` as a new biological process term under `macroautophagy`\n+- Added exact synonym `ferritin-specific autophagy`\n+- Used a concise standardized definition consistent with existing selective macroautophagy terms in GO\n+- Supported the term with PMID:25327288, PMID:26436293, and PMID:38714719\n+\n+Validation:\n+- `make travis_build` passed before and after the edit\n+\n+Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Added a new GO biological process term for ferritin-selective macroautophagy.\n+\n+Change made:\n+- Added `GO:7770069` `ferritinophagy`\n+  - def: `The selective degradation of ferritin by macroautophagy.`\n+  - synonym: `ferritin-specific autophagy` EXACT\n+  - parent: `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy`\n+  - tracker: `https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30894`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- The issue request and follow-up curator comment converged on the community label `ferritinophagy` with `ferritin-specific autophagy` as the exact synonym.\n+- Existing GO precedent for cargo-specific selective macroautophagy terms uses simple asserted classification under `macroautophagy` with concise definitions of the form `The selective degradation of X by macroautophagy.`\n+- I followed that pattern rather than adding `intersection_of` axioms, because there is no clear dedicated DOSDP for this subclass and stronger logical equivalence would add unnecessary specificity.\n+\n+References reviewed:\n+- PMID:25327288: identifies NCOA4-mediated selective autophagy of ferritin and links the process to iron homeostasis.\n+- PMID:26436293: explicitly uses the term `ferritinophagy` and supports NCOA4 as a selective cargo receptor delivering ferritin to lysosomes via autophagosomes.\n+- PMID:38714719: provides recent support for the wording `ferritin-specific autophagic pathway` and the release of iron stored in ferritin.\n+\n+Validation performed:\n+- Pre-change validation: `cd src/ontology && make travis_build`\n+- Post-change validation: `cd src/ontology && make travis_build`\n+- Reference support text validated with `linkml-reference-validator`\n+\n+Checklist:\n+- [x] PLAN: issue context reviewed and intent clear\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: ontology validated before edits\n+- [x] RESEARCH: supporting literature reviewed and summarized in `RESEARCH.md`\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: relevant GO autophagy terms and precedent reviewed\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: precedent documented in `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md`\n+- [x] EDITS: new term added through `terms/` and checked in with `obo-checkin.pl`\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: parentage set to `macroautophagy`; no over-specified axioms added\n+- [x] METADATA: namespace, definition, tracker item, `created_by`, and `creation_date` included for the new term\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed after changes\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: PMID support checked and validated\n+- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: ontology edit committed locally\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,12 @@\n+Added the requested term and committed the ontology change locally.\n+\n+Summary:\n+- Added `ferritinophagy` as a new biological process term under `macroautophagy`\n+- Added exact synonym `ferritin-specific autophagy`\n+- Used a concise standardized definition consistent with existing selective macroautophagy terms in GO\n+- Supported the term with PMID:25327288, PMID:26436293, and PMID:38714719\n+\n+Validation:\n+- `make travis_build` passed before and after the edit\n+\n+Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+Added a new GO biological process term for ferritin-selective macroautophagy.\n+\n+Change made:\n+- Added `GO:7770069` `ferritinophagy`\n+  - def: `The selective degradation of ferritin by macroautophagy.`\n+  - synonym: `ferritin-specific autophagy` EXACT\n+  - parent: `GO:0016236 ! macroautophagy`\n+  - tracker: `https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30894`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- The issue request and follow-up curator comment converged on the community label `ferritinophagy` with `ferritin-specific autophagy` as the exact synonym.\n+- Existing GO precedent for cargo-specific selective macroautophagy terms uses simple asserted classification under `macroautophagy` with concise definitions of the form `The selective degradation of X by macroautophagy.`\n+- I followed that pattern rather than adding `intersection_of` axioms, because there is no clear dedicated DOSDP for this subclass and stronger logical equivalence would add unnecessary specificity.\n+\n+References reviewed:\n+- PMID:25327288: identifies NCOA4-mediated selective autophagy of ferritin and links the process to iron homeostasis.\n+- PMID:26436293: explicitly uses the term `ferritinophagy` and supports NCOA4 as a selective cargo receptor delivering ferritin to lysosomes via autophagosomes.\n+- PMID:38714719: provides recent support for the wording `ferritin-specific autophagic pathway` and the release of iron stored in